salinity Changelog
===============

Here you can see the full list of changes between each salinity release.

Version 0.3.6
-------------
- New dockerfile for debian9 with systemd
- Can return status of highstate (easier to automate testing) 

Version 0.3.4
-------------
- Reorganize dockerfiles : each image has a directory
- Add handling of image key in salinity.yml file, and default to debian-latest

Version 0.3.3
-------------
- Added docker option to activate port mapping
- Moving Docker hub repository to organization igbmc
- Freeze Saltstack server/minion version to 2015.8.10 (for debian 7) and 2015.8.11 (for debian 8)
- Removing boot2docker usage (thank you Docker for full feature tools on Mac !)

Version 0.3.2
-------------
- Added --image option. Salinity now support testing on Debian 7 or Debian 8
- Salinity now uses images hosted on Docker Hub under in the namespace `salinity`

Version 0.3.1
-------------
- Fixed --verbose option

Version 0.3.0
-------------

- Added support for YAML configuration file
- Added --pubkey and --privkey options to test command for access to formula secured git repositories
- Added --use_default_keys options to test command for access to formula secured git repositories
- Remove publickey command
- Rewrite README
